{"type":"message","id":"02897df3","parentId":"a09107ab","timestamp":"2026-04-12T11:19:40.494Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6kgw9ius9ku8_1","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n      \"agentId\": \"master-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"name\": \"5p Progress Report\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775975347574,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775992518379,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 300000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1775975347574\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are the 5-minute status reporter for the OpenClaw 34-agent ecosystem.\\n\\nCheck sessions_list and report pipeline status to group -5212380728.\\n\\nFormat:\\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Status | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\n✅ Pipeline: HEALTHY\\n• Active sessions: N | Running agents: list\\n• MCP servers: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron jobs: 2 active (5p every 5m | Daily @ 5AM+7)\\n• Blockers: none\\n\\nOnly report if any agent status = failed or blocked. Otherwise send HEARTBEAT_OK.\\n\\nIf everything is healthy, send nothing (no message to group) — stay silent.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"-5212380728\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1775992760901,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775992460901,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 57478,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"runningAtMs\": 1775992760908\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"agentId\": \"master-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"name\": \"5p Progress Report - DTLX\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775986516041,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775992705430,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 300000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1775986440000\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are the 5-minute status reporter for the AHV DTLX project ecosystem.\\n\\nCheck sessions_list and report pipeline status to group -5168104492.\\n\\nFormat:\\n🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Status | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\n✅ Pipeline: HEALTHY\\n• Active sessions: N\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅\\n\\nIf everything is healthy, send nothing — stay silent.\\nIf any agent failed, report the failure.\\n\\nOnly send to group -5168104492 when there is something to report.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"-5168104492\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1775992954943,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775992654943,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 50487,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"53c5832a-eecc-4d6b-a4c3-d1b78a430dca\",\n      \"agentId\": \"master-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775975353622,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775975353622,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 5 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Orbis, the Global Orchestrator. Send a morning briefing to the Telegram group -5212380728 covering: (1) Yesterday's completed tasks, (2) Today's priorities, (3) Any blockers or risks. Format as a clean status report. Sign as Orbis 🌐.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"-5212380728\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1776031200000\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"1efacff3-ca8a-47c8-9490-3a12df8f1df5\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"pet-connect-dev-stall-monitor\",\n      \"description\": \"Monitor Pet Connect developer progress and alert if development appears stalled or not progressing.\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775783758784,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775789898684,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 900000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1775783758784\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check Pet Connect developer progress in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/03-development. Focus on whether the developer appears stalled or not making progress. Inspect recent file changes in docs and src/pet-connect, especially IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_V2.md, HANDOVER.md, prisma/, src/domain/, src/application/, src/infrastructure/, and other new code. If there are signs of progress, stay silent. If developer output appears stalled, inconsistent, or not moving for too long, send a concise alert to Khuowgn with blocker/risk summary and what needs intervention. Do not ask the user questions unless intervention is truly required.\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775789158825,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 55162,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"20f15566-d965-48e3-840f-ee1192cee726\",\n      \"agentId\": \"developer\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"bootstrap-backup-ui-scale-adjustment-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775879641463,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775880332761,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-11T03:53:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:driving-system-bootstrap-developer\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project: teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup\\nActive repo for implementation:\\n- FE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe\\n- BE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\\n\\nNew user task:\\n\\\"I need to adjust the current system’s overall screen size and font size. On my current window, I have to scale it down to 80% for it to look right, so please help me implement this adjustment.\\\"\\n\\nYou are in the project-scoped developer session for bootstrap-backup. Follow current SOUL/AGENTS rules, including OpenSpec-first for significant work.\\n\\nRequired approach:\\n1. Check whether this UI scaling change is best implemented via root typography/base layout/container scale tokens, not one-off page hacks.\\n2. Because project has OpenSpec available, create or align to minimal OpenSpec change/spec context first if none exists yet.\\n3. Then implement the FE change.\\n4. Prefer system-wide, maintainable adjustment over per-page patching.\\n5. Avoid breaking responsive behavior.\\n6. Verify by running the FE and checking the affected root layout/theme/global CSS files.\\n7. Write/update handover with exact files changed and short rationale.\\n\\nExpected output back to Orbis:\\n- diagnosis of root cause\\n- implementation approach chosen\\n- exact files changed\\n- whether change is global or partial\\n- any risks / follow-up QA notes\\n\\nDo the work now.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1800\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775880052010,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 280751,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"43dc76cd-a867-4619-b773-3f6e59ebb6f7\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"ahv-driving-backend-qa-audit-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775865358843,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775866022055,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T23:56:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project root: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\\n\\nYou are QA Reviewer. Do not implement code. Audit backend quality/risk only.\\n\\nScope:\\n- Review request flow, error flow, auth middleware usage, validation coverage, logging consistency, env/config hygiene, and obvious performance/code-quality risks.\\n- Review key modules and entrypoints for defects or operational risk.\\n- Flag security smells, maintainability issues, runtime fragility, and missing test coverage signals.\\n- Do not rewrite code. Report only.\\n\\nDeliverables to write in your workspace docs:\\n1) BACKEND_QA_AUDIT_AHV_DRIVING.md\\n2) BACKEND_RISK_MATRIX_AHV_DRIVING.md\\n3) HANDOVER.md\\n\\nRequired output structure:\\n- Executive summary\\n- Critical findings\\n- Medium findings\\n- Low findings\\n- Risk matrix (severity, area, evidence, impact, recommendation)\\n- Fast wins\\n- Needs runtime confirmation\\n- Brutal truth summary\\n\\nBe evidence-based from files. If something is uncertain, label it clearly.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1800\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775865798408,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 223647,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ad7f8cd3-5b36-4054-95ef-bee3f6bc4753\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"ahv-driving-architecture-audit-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775865358813,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775865798408,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T23:56:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project root: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\\n\\nYou are Architect. Do not implement code. Audit the backend architecture and the branch's migration shape.\\n\\nScope:\\n- Read the real repo structure and key files.\\n- Determine how much of the system is truly clean architecture vs hybrid/legacy module structure.\\n- Trace layering: app/common/modules/domain/infrastructure/config/middlewares.\\n- Identify architectural violations, dependency direction problems, mixed concerns, and migration risks.\\n- Evaluate whether branch name feature/clean-architecture-migration matches reality.\\n- Suggest a realistic migration strategy from current state, but do not modify code.\\n\\nDeliverables to write in your workspace docs:\\n1) ARCHITECTURE_AUDIT_AHV_DRIVING.md\\n2) HANDOVER.md\\n\\nRequired output structure:\\n- Current architecture snapshot\\n- Layer map\\n- Clean-architecture compliance assessment\\n- Hybrid/legacy hotspots\\n- Migration risks\\n- Recommended target architecture\\n- Phased remediation plan\\n- Brutal truth summary\\n\\nBe specific and evidence-based.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1800\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775865559740,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 238668,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c655ef85-59da-45cc-8544-d7fcc698218e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"pet-connect-frontend-progress-followup-5m\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775787213564,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775787555248,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T02:18:00.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Re-check Pet Connect frontend progress in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/03-development/src/pet-connect. Focus on frontend-demo implementation after the frontend-first override. Inspect recent changes in src/app, src/components, src/hooks, src/lib/mock-data.ts, docs/HANDOVER.md, and any new UI/demo files. Then send Khuowgn a concise blunt progress report in Vietnamese: what frontend surfaces are done, what is still missing for a demo, whether Dev is actually following the frontend-first direction, and whether intervention is needed. Do not ask questions unless truly blocked.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 600\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775787480004,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 75244,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ef82c238-0ea1-424b-8832-fc6debc753fe\",\n      \"agentId\": \"qa-reviewer\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"driving-system-qa-full-audit-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775831302194,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775831878204,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T14:27:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"You are Agent 04 — QA Reviewer for the driving-training system. Activate your relevant skills first, especially prompt-optimizer if applicable and your QA/review skills. This is a REPORT-ONLY audit. Do not modify frontend or backend code.\\n\\nProject roots:\\n- FE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe\\n- BE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\\n- PRD: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/PRD.md\\n- Shared context: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/PROJECT_CONTEXT_PACK.md\\n- Existing QA brief: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/04-qa-and-review/docs/TASK_BRIEF_API_UNUSED_FIELDS_AUDIT.md\\n\\nYour job: produce a QA report for the WHOLE driving-training system with separate frontend and backend findings, plus a system summary.\\n\\nRequired deliverables in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/04-qa-and-review/docs/:\\n1) DRIVING_SYSTEM_FE_QA_REPORT.md\\n2) DRIVING_SYSTEM_BE_QA_REPORT.md\\n3) DRIVING_SYSTEM_SYSTEM_QA_SUMMARY.md\\n4) API_UNUSED_FIELDS_REPORT.md\\n5) API_UNUSED_FIELDS_MATRIX.md\\n6) HANDOVER.md\\n\\nMinimum required content:\\n- Frontend report:\\n  - architecture/readability risks\\n  - route/page/component organization\\n  - state/data-fetching risks\\n  - FE↔API integration risks\\n  - UX consistency issues visible from code structure\\n  - top FE defects/risk list with severity\\n- Backend report:\\n  - controller/service/repository layering quality\\n  - logging consistency audit against current logger convention\\n  - validation/error-handling consistency\\n  - performance hotspot summary\\n  - security/sensitive-data handling observations\\n  - top BE defects/risk list with severity\\n- System summary:\\n  - end-to-end contract drift\\n  - highest-risk modules\\n  - release-blocker candidates\\n  - recommended remediation order\\n- API unused-fields audit:\\n  - follow existing QA brief strictly\\n  - report only, conservative evidence standard\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- No fixes.\\n- No code edits.\\n- Be brutally concrete, evidence-based, and cite file paths.\\n- If uncertain, label uncertainty explicitly.\\n- Focus on the currently implemented FE/BE, not hypothetical future scope.\\n\\nOutput quality bar:\\n- concise but hard-hitting\\n- tables where useful\\n- explicit severity labels: Critical / High / Medium / Low\\n- final HANDOVER must summarize status, audited modules, key findings, and what still needs runtime verification.\\n\\nWhen finished, write all deliverables and report completion succinctly.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 0,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775831304228,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 573976,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f1781cad-6f99-46c6-b31c-0986aac04518\",\n      \"agentId\": \"researcher\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:cron:ad7f8cd3-5b36-4054-95ef-bee3f6bc4753\",\n      \"name\": \"ahv-driving-backend-phase1-brainstorm\",\n      \"description\": \"Phase 1 brainstorming for AHV driving backend migration\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775896055582,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775896236201,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-11T08:28:00.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:ahv-driving-backend-research-phase1\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project root is locked to `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend`. This is the ONLY valid project context for this run. Do not use or reference any other project.\\n\\nTask: Phase 1 only — BRAINSTORM the migration step-by-step for this backend.\\n\\nGoal:\\n- We need a migration plan that will later flow as: brainstorming -> OpenSpec -> implementation.\\n- Your job now is ONLY brainstorming/research/planning input. Do NOT implement code. Do NOT write OpenSpec yet. Do NOT spill into another phase.\\n\\nRequired focus:\\n1. Inspect the backend structure and infer what migration is most likely needed based on current architecture.\\n2. Summarize current state brutally: legacy vs new structure, hotspots, migration pressure.\\n3. Propose 2-3 migration strategy options.\\n4. Recommend the best option with reasons.\\n5. Break the migration into staged steps that can later become OpenSpec tasks.\\n6. Identify risks, compatibility concerns, rollback points, and verification checkpoints.\\n7. Explicitly call out assumptions and unknowns.\\n\\nExpected output format:\\n- Project understanding\\n- Current architecture snapshot\\n- Migration problem statement\\n- 2-3 strategy options\\n- Recommended direction\\n- Step-by-step migration phases\\n- Risks / rollback / verification\\n- Open questions for Architect in next phase\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- Stay scoped to this project session only.\\n- No code changes.\\n- No spec creation yet.\\n- Concise but sharp.\\n\\nIf useful, inspect package.json, tsconfig, src tree, and route/module organization in the repo before answering.\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 900,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775896080016,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 156185,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"fdfdcd61-ac21-4635-9581-628963e8fb8e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"ahv-driving-route-map-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775865358779,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775865559740,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T23:56:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project root: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\\n\\nYou are Researcher. Do not implement code. Read the real backend repo and produce a route/module mapping report.\\n\\nScope:\\n- Identify the HTTP entry flow from src/server.ts -> src/app.ts -> route registration.\\n- Enumerate mounted route groups under /api/v1.\\n- Map each module to its main controller/service/route files.\\n- Group modules by business domain.\\n- Highlight naming inconsistencies, duplicate concepts, dead-looking surfaces, and likely legacy carryovers.\\n- Be evidence-based from files only.\\n\\nDeliverables to write in your workspace docs:\\n1) ROUTE_MAP_AHV_DRIVING.md\\n2) HANDOVER.md\\n\\nRequired output structure for ROUTE_MAP_AHV_DRIVING.md:\\n- Executive summary\\n- Entry flow\\n- Route/module inventory table\\n- Business-domain grouping\\n- Naming inconsistencies / legacy drift\\n- Unknowns / needs runtime confirmation\\n- Recommended next inspection targets\\n\\nUse concise markdown tables where possible. No filler.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1800\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 177586